React JS – Complete Concepts Guide with Definitions & Real-World Examples
1. What is React JS?
Definition: React is a JavaScript library used to build fast and interactive user interfaces (UI), especially Single Page Applications (SPAs).
Developed by: Meta Platforms
Real-world Example
Instagram Feed
Facebook News Feed
Netflix UI
WhatsApp Web
Instead of reloading the entire page, React updates only the changed parts.
2. Components
Definition: Components are reusable pieces of UI.
Example
JSX
function Welcome() {
  return <h1>Hello User</h1>;
}
Real-world Example
An e-commerce website:
Navbar Component
Product Component
Cart Component
Footer Component
Each section is a separate component.
3. JSX (JavaScript XML)
Definition: JSX allows writing HTML inside JavaScript.
Example
JSX
const element = <h1>Hello React</h1>;
Without JSX
JavaScript
React.createElement("h1", null, "Hello React");
Real-world Example
JSX
<div>
  <h1>Amazon</h1>
  <button>Add to Cart</button>
</div>
4. Props
Definition: Props are used to pass data from Parent Component to Child Component.
Example
JSX
function Student(props){
  return <h1>{props.name}</h1>;
}

<Student name="Krishna" />
Real-world Example
Employee Details:
JSX
<Employee
 name="Hari"
 designation="Developer"
/>
5. State
Definition: State stores dynamic data inside a component.
Example
JSX
import { useState } from "react";

function Counter(){
 const [count,setCount] = useState(0);

 return(
   <>
    <h1>{count}</h1>
    <button onClick={() => setCount(count+1)}>
      Increment
    </button>
   </>
 );
}
Real-world Example
Shopping Cart Count
Login Status
Notification Count
6. Event Handling
Definition: React handles user actions like click, submit, hover.
Example
JSX
function App(){

 function clickMe(){
   alert("Button Clicked");
 }

 return(
   <button onClick={clickMe}>
      Click
   </button>
 );
}
Real-world Example
Login Button
Search Button
Payment Button
7. Conditional Rendering
Definition: Displaying UI based on conditions.
Example
JSX
function App(){

 const isLoggedIn = true;

 return(
   <>
   {isLoggedIn ? <h1>Welcome</h1> : <h1>Login</h1>}
   </>
 );
}
Real-world Example
Netflix:
User logged in → Show Movies
User not logged in → Show Login Page
8. Lists and Keys
Definition: Used to render multiple items.
Example
JSX
const fruits = ["Apple","Banana","Mango"];

function App(){
 return(
   <ul>
    {fruits.map((fruit,index)=>
      <li key={index}>{fruit}</li>
    )}
   </ul>
 );
}
Real-world Example
Product Listings
Student Records
Employee Data
9. Forms
Definition: Used to collect user input.
Example
JSX
function App(){

 const [name,setName] = useState("");

 return(
   <input
     value={name}
     onChange={(e)=>setName(e.target.value)}
   />
 );
}
Real-world Example
Login Form
Registration Form
Feedback Form
10. Controlled Components
Definition: Form data controlled by React State.
Example
JSX
<input
 value={name}
 onChange={(e)=>setName(e.target.value)}
/>
Real-world Example
Registration Page Validation.
11. useState Hook
Definition: Manages state in functional components.
Example
JSX
const [age,setAge] = useState(20);
Real-world Example
Counter
Cart Quantity
Toggle Menu
12. useEffect Hook
Definition: Performs side effects after rendering.
Example
JSX
useEffect(()=>{
 console.log("Component Loaded");
},[]);
Real-world Example
